# @simpill/env.utils - Cursor Rules

## Package Identity

Type-safe environment variable utility library for Node.js and Edge runtimes.
This is a **utility package**, not a frontend application.

## Architecture

### Runtime Separation (Strict)

- `src/client/` - Edge/browser safe. No `fs`, no `process.env` writes.
- `src/server/` - Full Node.js. File system, dotenvx, process.env extension.
- `src/shared/` - Pure functions only. Zero runtime dependencies.

### Design Patterns

- **Singleton**: `EnvManager.getInstance()` for consistent state
- **Lazy initialization**: Auto-bootstrap on first access
- **Type-safe getters**: `getString`, `getNumber`, `getBoolean` with defaults
- **Strict variants**: `getNumberStrict`, `getBooleanStrict` throw on parse failure

## Code Standards

### TypeScript

- Strict mode required. No `any`, no unsafe casts.
- Explicit return types on public APIs.
- Use `readonly` for immutable properties and parameters.
- Prefer `as const` objects over enums.
- Document `@throws` for methods that throw.

### Naming

| Type | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| Classes | PascalCase | `EnvManager` |
| Functions | camelCase | `parseBooleanEnvValue` |
| Constants | SCREAMING_SNAKE | `DEFAULT_ENV_PATHS` |
| Files | dot-separated | `env.utils.ts` |
| Tests | `{name}.{type}.test.ts` | `env-manager.unit.test.ts` |

### Style

- 2-space indent, double quotes, semicolons
- 100 character line width
- Max 400 lines per file
- Biome for lint/format: `npm run check:fix`

## Testing

### Structure

```
__tests__/
â”œâ”€â”€ client/unit/
â”œâ”€â”€ server/unit/
â”œâ”€â”€ server/integration/
â”œâ”€â”€ shared/unit/
â””â”€â”€ fixtures/
```

### Requirements

- 80% coverage minimum (branches, functions, lines, statements)
- Jest with ts-jest
- Use `EnvManager.resetInstance()` between tests
- Mock file system for integration tests
- Test both success and error paths

### Test Patterns

```typescript
// AAA pattern
describe("EnvManager", () => {
  beforeEach(() => {
    EnvManager.resetInstance();
  });

  it("returns default when key missing", () => {
    // Arrange
    const manager = EnvManager.getInstance();
    
    // Act
    const result = manager.getString("MISSING_KEY", "default");
    
    // Assert
    expect(result).toBe("default");
  });
});
```

## Error Handling

- Use custom errors from `src/shared/errors.ts`
- `MissingEnvError` - required variable not set
- `EnvParseError` - value cannot be parsed to expected type
- `EnvDecryptError` - decryption failure
- Never swallow errors silently

## Constants

- Centralize in `src/shared/constants.ts`
- No magic strings or numbers in business logic
- Use typed const objects:

```typescript
export const NODE_ENV = {
  DEVELOPMENT: "development",
  PRODUCTION: "production",
  TEST: "test",
} as const;

export type NodeEnv = typeof NODE_ENV[keyof typeof NODE_ENV];
```

## Commands

```bash
npm run build          # Compile to dist/
npm test               # Run Jest
npm run test:coverage  # Coverage report
npm run check:fix      # Fix lint + format
npm run verify         # All pre-push checks
npx tsc --noEmit       # Type check only
```

## Definition of Done

- [ ] Type checks clean (`npx tsc --noEmit`)
- [ ] All tests pass
- [ ] Coverage >= 95%
- [ ] No lint errors (`npm run lint`)
- [ ] Public APIs have JSDoc with `@throws` where applicable
- [ ] No `any` types
- [ ] No magic literals
- [ ] DRY Patterns applied
- [ ] Fully strongly typed
- [ ] No AI Slop
